    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="18"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d18">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 182/1</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State</hi>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d18fn2">The original of this undated memorandum is in
                        Secretary <persName corresp="#p_LR1">Lansing</persName>’s hand and is
                        accompanied by other manuscript memoranda on subjects for consideration. The
                        latter are not printed.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian"
                        notAfter="1917-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1917-09-15T00:00:00-05:00"
                        >undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Queries</hi>
                </p>
                <p>How far should the United States take part in the determination of European
                    boundaries?</p>
                <p>How far should the United States take part in the redistribution of colonial
                    possession?</p>
                <p>Should the United States go further than to approve or disapprove an agreed
                    boundary on any other ground than that it contains an element of future
                    discord?</p>
                <p>Should the basis of territorial distribution be race, language, religion or
                    previous political affiliation?</p>
                <pb facs="0082" n="12" xml:id="pg_12"/>
                <p>Where two or more countries have political claims to a particular territory, as
                    in Macedonia, what should be the basis of settlement? If it is determined that
                    the preponderance of a particular nationality in the population is controlling
                        <hi rend="italic">prima facie</hi>, how far should conquest or enforced
                    colonization affect such basis? (This might apply to Alsace-Lorraine,
                    Schleswig-Holstein and the region about Dantzig.)</p>
                <p>Should colonial possessions be guaranteed to the power holding them without a
                    limitation as to the character of the government, commercial freedom, and
                    economic opportunity to other nations?</p>
            </div>
        </body>
